table itertools_extra88.names_group2:
  description: "accumulate/groupby/islice/starmap __name__ strings; all C types in itertoolsmodule.c; wave 250; new to extra88"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: string_identity
  id_prefix: itertoolsnames88

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [accumulate_name_eq_accumulate,
       accumulate.__name__.__eq__,
       ["accumulate"],
       true,
       "itertools.accumulate.__name__.__eq__('accumulate') == True — accumulate is a C extension type in Modules/itertoolsmodule.c that makes an iterator returning accumulated sums or other binary function results; __name__ is 'accumulate' (10 chars); str.__eq__('accumulate') returns True; prior spec extra87 checked accumulate.__mro__.__len__() and __bases__[0].__name__; this spec (extra88) checks __name__; new to extra88"]
    - [groupby_name_eq_groupby,
       groupby.__name__.__eq__,
       ["groupby"],
       true,
       "itertools.groupby.__name__.__eq__('groupby') == True — groupby is a C extension type in Modules/itertoolsmodule.c that makes an iterator returning consecutive keys and groups from an iterable; __name__ is 'groupby' (7 chars); str.__eq__('groupby') returns True; prior spec extra87 checked groupby.__mro__.__len__(); this spec (extra88) checks __name__; new to extra88"]
    - [islice_name_eq_islice,
       islice.__name__.__eq__,
       ["islice"],
       true,
       "itertools.islice.__name__.__eq__('islice') == True — islice is a C extension type in Modules/itertoolsmodule.c that makes an iterator returning selected elements from an iterable; __name__ is 'islice' (6 chars); str.__eq__('islice') returns True; prior spec extra87 checked islice.__mro__.__len__(); this spec (extra88) checks __name__; new to extra88"]
    - [starmap_name_eq_starmap,
       starmap.__name__.__eq__,
       ["starmap"],
       true,
       "itertools.starmap.__name__.__eq__('starmap') == True — starmap is a C extension type in Modules/itertoolsmodule.c that makes an iterator computing a function using arguments obtained from an iterable; __name__ is 'starmap' (7 chars); str.__eq__('starmap') returns True; prior spec extra87 checked starmap.__bases__[0].__name__; this spec (extra88) checks __name__; new to extra88"]

